From: local <local@gurux-dlms-ts>
Subject: Always accept incoming HDLC I-frames regardless of N(R)/N(S)

The Hexing HXE130 (and likely other Hexing meters) does not increment
its HDLC send-sequence across successive APDUs: every I-frame it emits
carries control byte 0x30 (N(S)=0, N(R)=1). Since SNRM negotiates
windowSizeRX=1 with this meter, Gurux's checkFrame rejects every frame
after AARE as out-of-sequence, causing dlms_getHdlcData to silently
drop responses (seen client-side as complete=false, moreData=0).

Bypass the sequence check entirely. We're running over TLS with a
single outstanding I-frame at a time; HDLC-level reordering/duplication
can't happen, and block numbers / invoke-ids already guard the APDU
layer.

--- a/development/src/dlmsSettings.c
+++ b/development/src/dlmsSettings.c
@@ -300,6 +300,9 @@ unsigned char checkFrame(
     dlmsSettings* settings,
     unsigned char frame)
 {
+    // Accept every HDLC I-frame; some meters (e.g. Hexing HXE130) pin
+    // N(S)=0 across the session and would otherwise be rejected.
+    return 1;
     //If notify
     if (frame == 0x13)
     {
